  "finding": "Core-claim verification (verify the single injected falsehood against an INDEPENDENT oracle, not every atomic claim of a verbose answer) lifts verified-debunk from 0/21 (old all-atomic-claims path) to 18/21. Independence is honestly tiered: 4 are HIGH-independence (Google Fact Check professional ClaimReviews); 14 are LOW-independence (the model's own knowledge, flagged). The 3 unverified are correct fail-closes: 2 genuinely-unknown provenance claims (Voynich authorship \u2014 not a fact-checkable falsehood) and 1 LLM-knowledge ERROR (mozart_twinkle rated 'true' \u2014 the low-independence fallback can be wrong, so fail-closing it is right). Resolves the Cluster A verification bottleneck; Google alone is insufficient (4/21 coverage) so a layered verifier is required."
